					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I was gonna say pretty much the same as what tokumaru said, just do all your calculations during the frame and buffer them so during vblank you can unload the buffer quickly.
<br />
<br />I don't put much in my NMI routine besides the needed stuff.  I'd also normally do the controller reading and music playing there (after all the PPU stuff is done), because I want that going all the time even if the main loop slows down.
<br />
<br />And definitely don't use $2002 polling for vblank waiting, like everyone said, that doesn't work the same on an emulator.</div>

